: \"the scene\", \"from\": 2273, \"to\": 2282}, {\"ngram\": \"social media\", \"from\": 2286, \"to\": 2298}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"mocking\", \"from\": 2347, \"to\": 2359}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some Greek Orthodox Church representatives also denounced the opening as \\\"blasphemous.\\\"\", \"from\": 2378, \"to\": 2465, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2383, \"end\": 2404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eastern_Orthodox_Church\", \"score\": 0.999999998493422, \"rank\": 1.5066766307670194e-09, \"text\": \"Greek Orthodox Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eastern_Orthodox_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eastern_Orthodox_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the opening\", \"from\": 2436, \"to\": 2447}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the ceremony's artistic director, Thomas Jolly, clarified that the tableau was not inspired byThe Last Supper.On the contrary, it represented the Greek god Dionysus arriving at a celebration the gods of Olympus were throwing.\", \"from\": 2467, \"to\": 2702, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2510, \"end\": 2516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"score\": 0.9999999965089046, \"rank\": 3.4833793650016428e-09, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\"}, {\"begin\": 2623, \"end\": 2628, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.9379361443589234, \"rank\": 0.03851082679938477, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}, {\"begin\": 2633, \"end\": 2641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1889641365179773e-37, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}, {\"begin\": 2680, \"end\": 2687, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.2858690893451073e-12, \"text\": \"Olympus\", \"types\": [\"Q8502\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the ceremony's artistic director\", \"from\": 2476, \"to\": 2508}, {\"ngram\": \"the tableau\", \"from\": 2539, \"to\": 2550}, {\"ngram\": \"Last Supper\", \"from\": 2574, \"to\": 2585}, {\"ngram\": \"the contrary\", \"from\": 2589, \"to\": 2601}, {\"ngram\": \"a celebration\", \"from\": 2653, \"to\": 2666}, {\"ngram\": \"the gods\", \"from\": 2667, \"to\": 2675}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jolly stated he did not intend to be \\\"subversive,\\\" or to \\\"mock,\\\" or \\\"shock.\\\"\", \"from\": 2703, \"to\": 2779, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He said he was trying to convey France's values of freedom and inclusion.\", \"from\": 2780, \"to\": 2853, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2812, \"end\": 2818, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8853639673855206, \"rank\": 0.12705491806729136, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"freedom\", \"from\": 2831, \"to\": 2838}, {\"ngram\": \"inclusion\", \"from\": 2843, \"to\": 2852}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jolly further insisted the tableau was not a reference toThe Last Supper.Instead, it was a nod toa pagan celebration featuring Dionysus.Jolly explained, \\\"The idea was to create a big pagan party in line with the god of Mount Olympus.\", \"from\": 2855, \"to\": 3088, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3074, \"end\": 3087, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.09601829322382e-30, \"text\": \"Mount Olympus\", \"types\": [\"Q8502\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the tableau\", \"from\": 2878, \"to\": 2889}, {\"ngram\": \"a reference\", \"from\": 2898, \"to\": 2909}, {\"ngram\": \"a nod toa pagan celebration\", \"from\": 2944, \"to\": 2971}, {\"ngram\": \"Dionysus\", \"from\": 2982, \"to\": 2990}, {\"ngram\": \"Jolly\", \"from\": 2991, \"to\": 2996}, {\"ngram\": \"The idea\", \"from\": 3009, \"to\": 3017}, {\"ngram\": \"a big pagan party\", \"from\": 3032, \"to\": 3049}, {\"ngram\": \"line\", \"from\": 3053, \"to\": 3057}, {\"ngram\": \"the god\", \"from\": 3063, \"to\": 3070}]}, {\"sentence\": \"My wish is not to be subversive, nor to mock or to shock.\", \"from\": 3089, \"to\": 3146, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"My wish\", \"from\": 3089, \"to\": 3096}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most of all, I wanted to senda message of love,a message of inclusionand not at all to divide.\\\"\", \"from\": 3147, \"to\": 3242, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"message\", \"from\": 3178, \"to\": 3185}, {\"ngram\": \"love\", \"from\": 3189, \"to\": 3193}, {\"ngram\": \"a message\", \"from\": 3194, \"to\": 3203}, {\"ngram\": \"inclusionand\", \"from\": 3207, \"to\": 3219}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jolly told BFMTV, \\\"You will never find in me, or in my work, a desire to mock or denigrate anyone.\", \"from\": 3244, \"to\": 3342, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3255, \"end\": 3260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BFM_TV\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"BFMTV\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BFM_TV\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BFM_TV\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my work\", \"from\": 3296, \"to\": 3303}, {\"ngram\": \"a desire\", \"from\": 3305, \"to\": 3313}, {\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 3335, \"to\": 3341}]}, {\"sentence\": \"My aim was to create a ceremony that heals and reconciles, but also a ceremony that reaffirms the values which are those of our Republic of Liberty, Equality, Fraternity, and absolutely not to mock anyone.\\\"\", \"from\": 3343, \"to\": 3549, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"My aim\", \"from\": 3343, \"to\": 3349}, {\"ngram\": \"a ceremony\", \"from\": 3364, \"to\": 3374}, {\"ngram\": \"the values\", \"from\": 3437, \"to\": 3447}, {\"ngram\": \"our Republic\", \"from\": 3467, \"to\": 3479}, {\"ngram\": \"Liberty\", \"from\": 3483, \"to\": 3490}, {\"ngram\": \"Equality\", \"from\": 3492, \"to\": 3500}, {\"ngram\": \"Fraternity\", \"from\": 3502, \"to\": 3512}, {\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 3541, \"to\": 3547}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In an official statement, theInternational Olympic Committeeemphasized the importance of engaging with cultural narratives in a manner that fosters understanding rather than perpetuating stereotypes or offending communities.\", \"from\": 3551, \"to\": 3775, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an official statement\", \"from\": 3554, \"to\": 3575}, {\"ngram\": \"the importance\", \"from\": 3622, \"to\": 3636}, {\"ngram\": \"cultural narratives\", \"from\": 3654, \"to\": 3673}, {\"ngram\": \"a manner\", \"from\": 3677, \"to\": 3685}, {\"ngram\": \"stereotypes\", \"from\": 3738, \"to\": 3749}, {\"ngram\": \"offending communities\", \"from\": 3753, \"to\": 3774}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This acknowledgment serves as a reminder of the need for sensitively balancing the needs of individuals during an international event, as well as the need to engage in ongoing dialogue concerning the implications of artistic choices within a multicultural context.\", \"from\": 3776, \"to\": 4040, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This acknowledgment\", \"from\": 3776, \"to\": 3795}, {\"ngram\": \"a reminder\", \"from\": 3806, \"to\": 3816}, {\"ngram\": \"the need\", \"from\": 3820, \"to\": 3828}, {\"ngram\": \"the needs\", \"from\": 3855, \"to\": 3864}, {\"ngram\": \"individuals\", \"from\": 3868, \"to\": 3879}, {\"ngram\": \"an international event\", \"from\": 3887, \"to\": 3909}, {\"ngram\": \"the need\", \"from\": 3922, \"to\": 3930}, {\"ngram\": \"ongoing dialogue\", \"from\": 3944, \"to\": 3960}, {\"ngram\": \"the implications\", \"from\": 3972, \"to\": 3988}, {\"ngram\": \"artistic choices\", \"from\": 3992, \"to\": 4008}, {\"ngram\": \"a multicultural context\", \"from\": 4016, \"to\": 4039}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the actual wording of the apology sounds suspiciously like a non-apology - \\\"We are sorry you were offended,\\\" not \\\"We are sorry we made an offensive choice\\\" - it appears that the committee is willing to learn from this incident to make more thoughtful and respectful representation decisions for future ceremonies.\", \"from\": 4042, \"to\": 4361, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the actual wording\", \"from\": 4048, \"to\": 4066}, {\"ngram\": \"the apology\", \"from\": 4070, \"to\": 4081}, {\"ngram\": \"an offensive choice\", \"from\": 4183, \"to\": 4202}, {\"ngram\": \"the committee\", \"from\": 4222, \"to\": 4235}, {\"ngram\": \"this incident\", \"from\": 4261, \"to\": 4274}, {\"ngram\": \"more thoughtful and respectful representation decisions\", \"from\": 4283, \"to\": 4338}, {\"ngram\": \"future ceremonies\", \"from\": 4343, \"to\": 4360}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many Christians interpreted the tableau as a mockery of Leonardo da Vinci's iconic painting.\", \"from\": 4363, \"to\": 4455, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4368, \"end\": 4378, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9963402689134128, \"rank\": 0.003673157700233911, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\"}, {