re\": 0.9999996951597051, \"rank\": 3.048405776118524e-07, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the performance\", \"from\": 5159, \"to\": 5174}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 5229, \"to\": 5238}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some businesses, like the U.S. telecommunications providerC Spire, pulled their advertising from the Olympics broadcasts in response to the controversial scene.\", \"from\": 5241, \"to\": 5401, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Some businesses\", \"from\": 5241, \"to\": 5256}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S. telecommunications\", \"from\": 5263, \"to\": 5290}, {\"ngram\": \"providerC Spire\", \"from\": 5291, \"to\": 5306}, {\"ngram\": \"their advertising\", \"from\": 5315, \"to\": 5332}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics broadcasts\", \"from\": 5338, \"to\": 5361}, {\"ngram\": \"response\", \"from\": 5365, \"to\": 5373}, {\"ngram\": \"the controversial scene\", \"from\": 5377, \"to\": 5400}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even social media influencerAndrew Tate, who is currently facing trial in Romania on human trafficking and rape charges, criticized the Olympics for mocking Christianity and called on athletes to boycott the event.\", \"from\": 5402, \"to\": 5616, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5437, \"end\": 5441, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tate\", \"score\": 0.9999462896730547, \"rank\": 4.9891574535554623e-05, \"text\": \"Tate\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tate\"}, {\"begin\": 5476, \"end\": 5483, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Socialist_Republic_of_Romania\", \"score\": 0.5466762888882184, \"rank\": 0.70524469993936, \"text\": \"Romania\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Socialist_Republic_of_Romania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Socialist_Republic_of_Romania\"}, {\"begin\": 5559, \"end\": 5571, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9676654248276247, \"rank\": 0.03341503617126301, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Even social media\", \"from\": 5402, \"to\": 5419}, {\"ngram\": \"trial\", \"from\": 5467, \"to\": 5472}, {\"ngram\": \"human trafficking\", \"from\": 5487, \"to\": 5504}, {\"ngram\": \"rape charges\", \"from\": 5509, \"to\": 5521}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 5534, \"to\": 5546}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 5586, \"to\": 5594}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 5606, \"to\": 5615}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many of my Christian friends started sharing outraged comments and inflammatory memes hours after the opening ceremony took place.\", \"from\": 5618, \"to\": 5748, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5629, \"end\": 5638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999996951597051, \"rank\": 3.048405776118524e-07, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"outraged comments\", \"from\": 5663, \"to\": 5680}, {\"ngram\": \"inflammatory memes\", \"from\": 5685, \"to\": 5703}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 5716, \"to\": 5736}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 5742, \"to\": 5747}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The discussions lasted for days, and, as many Facebook discussions do, some of them turned rather heated.\", \"from\": 5749, \"to\": 5854, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The discussions\", \"from\": 5749, \"to\": 5764}, {\"ngram\": \"days\", \"from\": 5776, \"to\": 5780}, {\"ngram\": \"many Facebook discussions\", \"from\": 5790, \"to\": 5815}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However,some people arguedthat the outrage stemmed from a misunderstanding, as the tableau was intended to depict the ancient Greek god Dionysus and the Feast of Dionysus, rather than a direct reference to the Last Supper.\", \"from\": 5856, \"to\": 6078, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5974, \"end\": 5987, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greek_religion\", \"score\": 0.7710036652714833, \"rank\": 0.2954986581688271, \"text\": \"ancient Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greek_religion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greek_religion\"}, {\"begin\": 5992, \"end\": 6000, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1889641365179773e-37, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some people\", \"from\": 5864, \"to\": 5875}, {\"ngram\": \"the outrage\", \"from\": 5887, \"to\": 5898}, {\"ngram\": \"a misunderstanding\", \"from\": 5912, \"to\": 5930}, {\"ngram\": \"the tableau\", \"from\": 5935, \"to\": 5946}, {\"ngram\": \"the Feast\", \"from\": 6005, \"to\": 6014}, {\"ngram\": \"Dionysus\", \"from\": 6018, \"to\": 6026}, {\"ngram\": \"a direct reference\", \"from\": 6040, \"to\": 6058}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 6062, \"to\": 6077}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They suggested that the parallels drawn by Christians were due to the shared symbolism and iconography between Greek mythology and Christianity.\", \"from\": 6079, \"to\": 6223, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6122, \"end\": 6132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9963402689134128, \"rank\": 0.003673157700233911, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 6190, \"end\": 6205, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.9999972870742078, \"rank\": 2.712933304096373e-06, \"text\": \"Greek mythology\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}, {\"begin\": 6210, \"end\": 6222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9676654248276247, \"rank\": 0.03341503617126301, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the parallels\", \"from\": 6099, \"to\": 6112}, {\"ngram\": \"the shared symbolism\", \"from\": 6145, \"to\": 6165}, {\"ngram\": \"iconography\", \"from\": 6170, \"to\": 6181}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Moving forward, this controversy might lead to more thoughtful considerations about the use of religious imagery in secular contexts, aiming to foster understanding and respect across different beliefs and perspectives.\", \"from\": 6225, \"to\": 6444, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this controversy\", \"from\": 6241, \"to\": 6257}, {\"ngram\": \"more thoughtful considerations\", \"from\": 6272, \"to\": 6302}, {\"ngram\": \"the use\", \"from\": 6309, \"to\": 6316}, {\"ngram\": \"religious imagery\", \"from\": 6320, \"to\": 6337}, {\"ngram\": \"secular contexts\", \"from\": 6341, \"to\": 6357}, {\"ngram\": \"understanding\", \"from\": 6376, \"to\": 6389}, {\"ngram\": \"respect\", \"from\": 6394, \"to\": 6401}, {\"ngram\": \"different beliefs\", \"from\": 6409, \"to\": 6426}, {\"ngram\": \"perspectives\", \"from\": 6431, \"to\": 6443}]}, {\"sentence\": \"1.\", \"from\": 6446, \"to\": 6448, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What is the controversy surrounding the Last Supper tableau at the 2024 Olympics?The controversy stems from a performance that Catholic leaders in France have criticized as a \\\"mockery of Christianity.\\\"\", \"from\": 6449, \"to\": 6650, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6576, \"end\": 6584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999980582288, \"rank\": 1.9417718304095054e-09, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 6596, \"end\": 6602, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8853639673855206, \"rank\": 0.12705491806729136, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 6636, \"end\": 6648, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9676654248276247, \"rank\": 0.03341503617126301, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the controversy\", \"from\": 6457, \"to\": 6472}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper tableau\", \"from\": 6485, \"to\": 6508}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Olympics?The controversy\", \"from\": 6512, \"to\": 6545}, {\"ngram\": \"a performance\", \"from\": 6557, \"to\": 6570}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"mockery\", \"from\": 6622, \"to\": 6632}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Conference of French bishops expressed deep regret over the depiction, which they viewed as derisive and mocking towards Christian beliefs.\", \"from\": 6651, \"to\": 6794, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6669, \"end\": 6675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999974774691492, \"rank\": 2.3494899002434355e-06, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 6776, \"end\": 6785, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999996951597051, \"rank\": 3.048405776118524e-07, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Conference\", \"from\": 6651, \"to\": 6665}, {\"ngram\": \"deep regret\", \"from\": 6694, \"to\": 6705}, {\"ngram\": \"the depiction\", \"from\": 6711, \"to\": 6724}]}, {\"sentence\": \"2.\", \"from\": 6796, \"to\": 6798, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Why has the Olympics' depiction of the Last Supper been criticized?Critics argue that the Olympics' show, directed by Thomas Jolly, included elements that mocked Leonardo da Vinci's famous painting, \\\"The Last Supper,\\\" which portrays Jesus Christ and his apostles.\", \"from\": 6799, \"to\": 7062, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6917, \"end\": 6923, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"score\": 0.9999999965089046, \"rank\": 3.4833793650016428e-09, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\"}, {\"begin\": 6961, \"end\": 6978, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3064942529007737e-37, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 7032, \"end\": 7044, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.2092302816861977e-12, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbped